laboratory_examinations.findings: Arterial oxygen saturation was 88% and partial pressure of oxygen was 56.3 mm Hg in room air.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: After embolization, arterial oxygen saturation improved to 98% and partial pressure of oxygen increased to 87.8 mm Hg.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Revealed a lobulated opacity with a large feeding artery and large draining veins.
Showed a large PAVF in the left ninth segment and a small PAVF near the main lesion.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Shunt ratio decreased from 32.7% to 9.8% after embolization.
